Saunders v. Chapin, Comptroller, et al. (Supreme Court, General Term, Second Department. February 11, 1889.) Appeal from special term, Kings county. Action by Joshua C. Saunders to enjoin the comptroller from conveying to the people certain land in Kings county. Defendants’ demurrers were sustained, and plaintiff appeals.

Argued before Barnard, P. J., and Dykman and Pratt, JJ.

George E. Pettit, for appellant. Charles F. Tabor, Atty. Gen., for respondents.

Order affirmed, with costs. Dykman, J., dissenting.
